Governor Aminu waziri Tambuwal has directed Islamic preachers and citizens of sokoto  state to observe special prayers for lasting peace in the neighbouring Zamfara state and other parts of the country. He gave the directive while hosting  the 23 local government council chairmen to a Ramadan breakfast  at the banquet hall of the presidential lodge Sokoto.  Tambuwal therefore charged Nigerians to take advantage of the holy month of Ramadan to pray for the country to surmount its  current security challenges .  The governor also stressed the need for leaders at all levels to show compassion to their followers.  "Allah is merciful to us as such we should be merciful to those under us ," he said He however expressed gratitude to the Sultan and other traditional rulers for fervently praying for  continuous peace and stability in sokoto state and the country at large.